uk.ac.cam.cl.intelligentgamedesigner.leveldesigner

Class LevelDesignerManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.SwingWorker
      • uk.ac.cam.cl.intelligentgamedesigner.leveldesigner.LevelDesignerManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, java.util.concurrent.Future, java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture

    public class LevelDesignerManager
extends javax.swing.SwingWorker
    This class serves as a middleman between the user interface and the LevelDesigner. It handles running and evaluating the performance of simulated players, and is used to initiate separate generation processes in the background.

      • isPhase1Complete

        public boolean isPhase1Complete(int threadID)
        This is a method used to synchronise the threads after completing phase 1. That is, the threads must wait until they've all completed phase 1 before they can start phase 2.
        Parameters:
        threadID - The identifier of the calling thread
        Returns:
